.

<br/>
<br/>
<b><big><a name="Derivative" id="Derivative">Derivative</a></big></b>
<br/>
CppAD computes the derivative of the <code><font color="blue">sign</font></code> function as zero for all
argument values 
<code><i><font color="black"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>x</span></font></i></code>
.
The correct mathematical derivative is different and
is given by

<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><mrow>
<msup><mrow><mstyle mathvariant='normal'><mi mathvariant='normal'>sign</mi>
</mstyle></mrow>
<mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
<mn>1</mn>
<mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
</mrow>
</msup>
<mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>x</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
<mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
<mn>2</mn>
<mi mathvariant='normal'>&#x003B4;</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>x</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
</mrow></math>

where 
<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><mrow>
<mi mathvariant='normal'>&#x003B4;</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>x</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
</mrow></math>

 is the Dirac Delta function.

